<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-2778] Use zero loss settings for producer in Kafka Connect</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2778</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The settings for the producer in Kafka Connect are not using zero loss settings (and was written before the client timeout patch, so would have been using outdated settings regardless). It should be updated to use settings that, by default, guarantee zero loss but can be overridden. In the case we do see an error, the task already exits.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
